1
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,120
I'm heading back.

2
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:45,840
Lawyer Xu,

3
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,480
the rain was pouring yesterday,

4
00:01:51,879 --> 00:01:52,760
and I got out of the car in a hurry.

5
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,879
I didn't get a chance to thank you.

6
00:01:56,719 --> 00:01:57,760
Thank you for driving me back.

7
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,239
It was on my way.

8
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,239
Wait a minute.

9
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:10,759
I'm ready.

10
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,120
Alright, alright.

11
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:12,800
I'm coming.

12
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,319
This is for you.

13
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,479
How to say goodbye properly?

14
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:47,039
Actually, he has helped me

15
00:02:48,439 --> 00:02:49,120
beyond

16
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,280
the obligation of a lawyer.

17
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,479
After the last meeting tomorrow,

18
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:57,520
I'll give him a gift.

19
00:02:58,719 --> 00:03:00,199
Ruan Yu at 28

20
00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:02,039
gives a gift

21
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,280
to Ruan Yu at 18

22
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,360
who didn't have the chance to give it.

23
00:03:05,479 --> 00:03:08,080
This ending is considered satisfactory, right?

24
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,360
The court trial tomorrow

25
00:03:13,159 --> 00:03:15,039
Lawyer Liu will be present.

26
00:03:16,599 --> 00:03:17,319
After today,

27
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:20,159
I may not see you anymore.

28
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,080
After all, you are usually

29
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,159
quite busy.

30
00:03:26,199 --> 00:03:27,759
Thank you for your help

31
00:03:28,719 --> 00:03:29,400
during this time.

32
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,560
Although Lawyer Liu said

33
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,719
you don't need to pay me,

34
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:37,919
I still want to

35
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:41,960
express my gratitude.

36
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:47,560
This is for you.

37
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,479
For you.

38
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,719
I hope that

39
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,720
your life and career

40
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,839
will go well

41
00:04:22,279 --> 00:04:23,360
in the future.

42
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:50,720
Thank you.

43
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,879
Who said we won't meet again?

44
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:20,680
I'll be there for tomorrow's trial.

45
00:05:57,439 --> 00:05:58,560
What does she mean?

46
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,120
What do you mean?

47
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:01,040
I want to know

48
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,399
what you mean.

49
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:22,000
First, she said we wouldn't meet again,

50
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:24,959
then she gave you a digital watch.

51
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:27,279
What does that mean?

52
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:31,120
The past is not worth lingering over.

53
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,879
Time will wash away everything.

54
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,519
Is it possible

55
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:38,600
that it means something else?

56
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:42,720
When Ruan Yu said there was no chance to meet again,

57
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,480
she wanted you to take the initiative

58
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,600
to create more opportunities to meet.

59
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:52,199
And the digital watch

60
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,879
was to express

61
00:06:54,879 --> 00:06:56,879
he cherishes the time

62
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:57,920
he spent with you.

63
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,879
Think about it.

64
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:07,759
Why did he give you an electronic watch

65
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,480
instead of a mechanical one?

66
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:11,519
What does Ruan Yu do?

67
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:13,439
He's a writer,

68
00:07:13,639 --> 00:07:14,680
playing with words.

69
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,800
There must be a meaning behind it.

70
00:07:21,639 --> 00:07:22,319
Think about it.

71
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,079
Think about it.

72
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,120
What does "electric" mean?

73
00:07:28,319 --> 00:07:29,879
It sounds like "miss".

74
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,240
Zi.

75
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,279
It means days.

76
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,759
Days, right?

77
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:37,720
Biao.

78
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:40,839
Biao.

79
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,319
Biao.

80
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:50,800
If you read "Biyao" fast,
it sounds like "Biao".

81
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:54,800
Biyao.

82
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,839
Right? What does it mean?

83
00:07:57,839 --> 00:07:59,480
It means that

84
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,759
with Ruan Yu,

85
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,199
were the days

86
00:08:02,199 --> 00:08:03,480
she had to remember.

87
00:08:03,959 --> 00:08:06,560
She's been keeping it in mind.

88
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,800
I finally made it.

89
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,759
If Ruan Yu plays with words like this,

90
00:08:10,759 --> 00:08:12,199
she would have long left the writer circle.

91
00:08:14,959 --> 00:08:15,480
In short,
in a word,

92
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,279
don't worry about what the watch

93
00:08:17,279 --> 00:08:17,839
means.
It's just a gift

94
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,439
is just a gesture.

95
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:20,959
Right?

96
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,439
If you really can't figure it out,

97
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:23,240
don't just sit here
overthinking it.

98
00:08:23,759 --> 00:08:24,480
Just ask her.
That's all there is to it.

99
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:32,879
Bro,

100
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,159
when it comes to court battles,

101
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:37,480
I can't beat you.

102
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,919
But in the realm of relationships,

103
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,639
I'm a veteran.

104
00:08:43,519 --> 00:08:44,919
in this field.

105
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:50,519
Didn't you see
my WeChat Moments yesterday?

106
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,360
My blind date

107
00:08:53,919 --> 00:08:54,840
was successful.

108
00:08:55,679 --> 00:08:56,480
We fell in love

109
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,759
at first sight,

110
00:08:58,759 --> 00:09:00,120
and we are very happy.

111
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,480
We will have a big family.

112
00:09:04,559 --> 00:09:05,960
If everything goes well,

113
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,519
we will...

114
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:14,840
Shanshan,

115
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,000
I'm not busy.

116
00:09:18,639 --> 00:09:19,519
Okay, okay.

117
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,159
The same restaurant

118
00:09:21,159 --> 00:09:22,360
you booked last time, right?

119
00:09:22,679 --> 00:09:23,639
Okay, no problem.

120
00:09:24,679 --> 00:09:25,919
Okay, okay.

121
00:09:26,679 --> 00:09:27,159
See you later.

122
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,519
Okay, bye.

123
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:30,879
I have to go.
I have something important to do.

124
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:32,480
I can't accompany you anymore.

125
00:09:36,279 --> 00:09:37,639
If you don't believe what I said,

126
00:09:40,399 --> 00:09:41,080
then don't
sneak around

127
00:09:41,799 --> 00:09:42,679
and ask her yourself.

128
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,320
Stubborn.

129
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,000
You think I'm like you,

130
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,399
so impatient?

131
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:10,000
Lawyer Xu,

132
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,120
why are you here?

133
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,120
I'll take you home.

134
00:11:25,919 --> 00:11:26,879
Why is the weather

135
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:28,600
always so miserable?

136
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,720
[This sudden downpour]

137
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,600
[is like an unexpected farewell,]

138
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,559
[seemingly without any warning,]

139
00:11:36,159 --> 00:11:37,960
[but the seeds of sorrow]

140
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,600
[have long been sown]

141
00:11:39,919 --> 00:11:41,759
[in the desolate air.]

142
00:11:46,399 --> 00:11:47,200
Why does the radio

143
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,919
always have ill intentions?

144
00:12:02,799 --> 00:12:04,120
Why would you give me this?

145
00:12:08,399 --> 00:12:09,519
I heard from Lawyer Liu

146
00:12:10,159 --> 00:12:11,559
that you often

147
00:12:11,559 --> 00:12:12,480
stay up late when busy.

148
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:13,879
I thought

149
00:12:14,159 --> 00:12:15,799
an electronic watch can monitor

150
00:12:15,799 --> 00:12:17,440
your blood pressure, heart rate

151
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,240
and other health data,

152
00:12:18,919 --> 00:12:20,519
so that it can remind you

153
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,720
to take care of yourself.

154
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:23,600
Don't be in a hurry.

155
00:12:23,919 --> 00:12:24,840
Wait and see.

156
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,320
Let's see if she will send you candies

157
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,799
when you are not busy.

158
00:12:32,519 --> 00:12:34,039
What's your intention?

159
00:12:38,039 --> 00:12:38,919
According to the professional ethics,

160
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,120
a lawyer can't accept
from clients.

161
00:12:41,759 --> 00:12:42,320
If you're
giving this to me

162
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,120
as a client,

163
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,519
I need to return it.

164
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:47,960
No, no.

165
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,000
You haven't even charged me,

166
00:12:50,639 --> 00:12:51,879
so technically,

167
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,879
you're not my lawyer yet.

168
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,320
Of course,

169
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,360
it's not from a client.

170
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:57,720
Then...

171
00:13:01,879 --> 00:13:02,559
Lawyer Xu,

172
00:13:03,519 --> 00:13:04,279
we can be

173
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,000
considered as friends, right?

174
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:09,559
Of course.

175
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:45,759
Hello, babe.

176
00:13:46,679 --> 00:13:47,440
Hello, Chuan.

177
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,000
Why did it take so long to answer?

178
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,159
Are you still at the company?

179
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,240
I was just busy.

180
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:53,759
Is your company

181
00:13:53,759 --> 00:13:54,960
humane at all?

182
00:13:55,039 --> 00:13:56,200
They're just picking on you.

183
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,879
I have no choice.

184
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,240
I have to do live streaming

185
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,279
and product selection myself.

186
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:03,159
And I have to attend some social events.

187
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:04,519
I'm almost

188
00:14:04,519 --> 00:14:05,559
a time management expert.

189
00:14:07,679 --> 00:14:08,679
It's late.

190
00:14:08,679 --> 00:14:10,000
You have to eat.

191
00:14:10,159 --> 00:14:10,799
I'll go right now.

192
00:14:10,919 --> 00:14:11,840
I'll eat later.

193
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:12,720
I'll hang up now.
I have to go.

194
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,200
Someone is waiting for you to eat.

195
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,200
My mom.

196
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:23,919
She's always afraid that I'm too busy
to eat.

197
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:26,759
Let's go.

198
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:31,120
Eat. Don't let your mom worry.

199
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,840
Aren't you afraid of being seen?

200
00:15:26,519 --> 00:15:27,799
So what if they see?

201
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,039
Baby, why are you here?

202
00:16:00,559 --> 00:16:01,559
I'm about to go to a meeting.

203
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,360
I saw you hadn't replied to my messages,

204
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,159
so I came up directly.

205
00:16:04,799 --> 00:16:05,320
Here.

206
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,360
I've been too busy today

207
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,320
to check my phone.

208
00:16:08,639 --> 00:16:09,720
I have a meeting to attend.

209
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,039
I can't be with you today.

210
00:16:14,519 --> 00:16:14,919
By the way,

211
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,639
did you park the car downstairs?

212
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,200
You can't park there.

213
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,200
You'll get a parking ticket.

214
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,519
You need to move it quickly.

215
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:21,799
One minute.

216
00:16:22,799 --> 00:16:24,159
I have no choice.

217
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:25,799
Fine.

218
00:16:25,799 --> 00:16:27,080
I can't stay with you today.

219
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,519
I'll go first.

220
00:16:30,679 --> 00:16:31,320
I'll go home with you.

221
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:33,720
Fine.

222
00:16:48,879 --> 00:16:49,559
Who is that?

223
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:53,519
A delivery guy.

224
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:54,679
No one took the order,

225
00:16:54,679 --> 00:16:55,759
so the merchant delivered it himself.

226
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:58,919
You said you were going back to the office to get something.

227
00:16:59,279 --> 00:17:00,279
Is it to get takeout?

228
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:01,759
Are you that hungry?

229
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:06,000
What do you think?

230
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,039
Thank you, Lawyer Xu.

231
00:17:14,759 --> 00:17:16,119
Drive slowly on your way back.

232
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,400
Lawyer Xu, do you have a stomachache?

233
00:17:33,559 --> 00:17:34,119
It's okay.

234
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:36,720
I've been tired all day,

235
00:17:37,319 --> 00:17:38,200
and I haven't had the chance to eat.

236
00:17:38,359 --> 00:17:39,839
I must be hungry, it's fine.

237
00:17:42,079 --> 00:17:42,839
Why don't you

238
00:17:44,519 --> 00:17:45,519
come up and eat something?

239
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:00,440
Come in.

240
00:18:05,319 --> 00:18:06,000
Lawyer Xu,

241
00:18:07,519 --> 00:18:08,319
You can wear this.

242
00:18:09,319 --> 00:18:10,039
It's new.

243
00:18:11,079 --> 00:18:12,599
I bought it last time

244
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,200
when you visited my home.

245
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:15,640
Thank you.

246
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,440
You should change your clothes.

247
00:18:27,119 --> 00:18:27,640
OK.

248
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,200
Please wait a minute.

249
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:31,759
OK.

250
00:19:16,799 --> 00:19:18,279
I bought it last time

251
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,920
when you visited my home.

252
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:23,000
Who visited my home?

253
00:19:43,319 --> 00:19:44,920
[He shouldn't have heard that.]

254
00:21:17,759 --> 00:21:18,759
Lawyer Xu, are you okay?

255
00:21:22,039 --> 00:21:22,519
I'm fine.

256
00:21:26,519 --> 00:21:27,359
Let me see.

257
00:21:27,359 --> 00:21:28,920
It's okay. I can do it myself.

258
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,160
Are you okay?

259
00:21:33,599 --> 00:21:34,119
I'm fine.

260
00:21:35,519 --> 00:21:36,480
The windows are closed.
It might be a bit stuffy.

261
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:38,960
I'll open them.

262
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:43,960
Maybe it's over there.

263
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:47,400
It's open.

264
00:21:48,079 --> 00:21:48,640
Yeah.

265
00:21:50,359 --> 00:21:51,359
I didn't sleep well

266
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,200
last night.

267
00:21:53,599 --> 00:21:54,359
I'm a little dizzy.

268
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,039
I'll take a break.

269
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:57,359
Lawyer Xu,

270
00:21:57,519 --> 00:21:58,720
take a break.

271
00:21:58,720 --> 00:21:59,680
I'll cook for you.

272
00:22:00,079 --> 00:22:01,160
Thank you.

273
00:22:02,559 --> 00:22:03,599
What do you want to eat?

274
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,400
Anything simple is fine.

275
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:07,240
I'll cook

276
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:08,359
some easy-to-digest noodles.

277
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:08,920
Okay.

278
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,039
Let me help you.

279
00:22:11,839 --> 00:22:12,640
No, no need.

280
00:22:13,079 --> 00:22:15,279
It only takes me five minutes to cook noodles.

281
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,880
You should rest.

282
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:20,720
Okay.

283
00:22:48,079 --> 00:22:49,240
Thank you, Mao.

284
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,519
Thank you for talking to me so much.

285
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,160
It's been a long time

286
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:57,400
since I've been this happy.

287
00:22:58,240 --> 00:23:00,640
If you have any problems in the future, just tell me.

288
00:23:02,359 --> 00:23:03,839
Don't keep it all inside.

289
00:23:05,279 --> 00:23:05,920
It's exhausting.

290
00:23:10,359 --> 00:23:11,160
Honestly,

291
00:23:12,799 --> 00:23:14,200
I've always been hesitant

292
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,000
to talk about

293
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,039
my family with others.

294
00:23:20,039 --> 00:23:20,880
It feels like

295
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,640
I'm constantly reopening

296
00:23:24,519 --> 00:23:26,880
my wounds

297
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,519
just to get sympathy.

298
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,119
But I don't want to hide anything from you.

299
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:37,039
Relationships are about two families,

300
00:23:38,519 --> 00:23:41,000
but marriage is about two families.

301
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:44,720
Although we

302
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:45,960
haven't gotten to that point yet,

303
00:23:48,599 --> 00:23:49,480
before,

304
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,960
when the people I went on blind dates with

305
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:53,400
found out about my family situation,

306
00:23:54,519 --> 00:23:56,160
they all backed out.

307
00:23:59,119 --> 00:24:00,240
I've already thought about

308
00:24:00,799 --> 00:24:01,799
being alone until I die.

309
00:24:02,319 --> 00:24:02,960
Shanshan,

310
00:24:03,759 --> 00:24:05,079
don't ever think like that.

311
00:24:05,559 --> 00:24:06,519
A girl as good as you

312
00:24:06,519 --> 00:24:07,839
how could you end up alone?

313
00:24:12,559 --> 00:24:13,880
It's not your fault.

314
00:24:14,559 --> 00:24:15,759
You've been through a lot.

315
00:24:16,799 --> 00:24:17,519
Don't worry.

316
00:24:17,519 --> 00:24:18,640
I don't care about your background,

317
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:19,880
or your family.

318
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:21,240
Right?

319
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,480
We're out of wine.
Waiter.

320
00:24:31,559 --> 00:24:32,039
Yes, sir?
Another bottle, please.

321
00:24:33,279 --> 00:24:33,759
Okay.

322
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,000
Lawyer Xu.

323
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:44,200
I'll take it.

324
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:45,759
Thank you.

325
00:24:46,759 --> 00:24:47,279
Okay.

326
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:54,119
Thanks.

327
00:24:59,079 --> 00:24:59,720
I'll take this call.

328
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:02,680
Hello?

329
00:25:06,839 --> 00:25:07,759
Send me the address.

330
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:08,720
I'll be there soon.

331
00:25:10,319 --> 00:25:10,759
Okay.

332
00:25:12,839 --> 00:25:13,680
What happened?

333
00:25:18,519 --> 00:25:19,359
Don't worry.

334
00:25:19,839 --> 00:25:21,039
I'm definitely not a scammer.

335
00:25:21,319 --> 00:25:21,880
It's okay, it's okay.

336
00:25:23,559 --> 00:25:25,000
My friend will be here soon.

337
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,119
He'll take care of this order.

338
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:26,920
Okay.

339
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:33,599
Why are your prices
so high at this restaurant?

340
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:35,960
Well,

341
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,799
you just opened three bottles

342
00:25:37,799 --> 00:25:39,119
of 2015 Harlan.

343
00:25:39,519 --> 00:25:41,880
The price per bottle is 25,999.

344
00:25:42,319 --> 00:25:44,200
25,999 per bottle?

345
00:25:44,559 --> 00:25:45,079
Yes.

346
00:25:47,559 --> 00:25:49,119
Why isn't it on the menu?

347
00:25:49,559 --> 00:25:50,039
No.

348
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,960
Everything in our restaurant

349
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:53,160
is

350
00:25:54,359 --> 00:25:55,160
clearly priced.

351
00:25:59,079 --> 00:26:00,279
What's wrong, Mao?

352
00:26:00,799 --> 00:26:01,440
Nothing.

353
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:02,759
Shanshan,

354
00:26:04,559 --> 00:26:05,720
where's my card?

355
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:06,759
It's over the limit.

356
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,039
Don't worry.

357
00:26:08,279 --> 00:26:09,359
I called my friend.

358
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:10,319
He'll be here soon
and take care of this.

359
00:26:11,799 --> 00:26:12,680
I can pay.

360
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:13,799
No, no, no.

361
00:26:14,799 --> 00:26:16,200
How could I let you pay?

362
00:26:17,279 --> 00:26:17,799
Listen to me.

363
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,000
Just go back and wait.

364
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,400
It'll be done soon.

365
00:26:53,039 --> 00:26:53,799
Are you still sober?

366
00:26:55,279 --> 00:26:56,079
Song.

367
00:26:57,599 --> 00:26:58,599
You're here.

368
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,480
Drink some water

369
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:03,640
and sober up.

370
00:27:08,200 --> 00:27:08,960
Are you here

371
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:10,319
to pay the bill for your friend?

372
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:12,000
Yes.

373
00:27:13,079 --> 00:27:14,440
May I see the receipt?

374
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:17,400
Thank you.

375
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:26,480
Do you know her?

376
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:27,519
No.

377
00:27:28,839 --> 00:27:29,240
Okay.

378
00:27:37,359 --> 00:27:38,240
Song,

379
00:27:39,559 --> 00:27:41,079
let me introduce.

380
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,799
This is Shanshan.

381
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:45,319
Shanshan,

382
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,839
this is my best friend,

383
00:27:48,279 --> 00:27:50,839
Xu Huaisong, Lawyer Xu.

384
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:53,880
Lawyer Xu, nice to meet you.

385
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,599
Brother Mao often talks about you.

386
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,960
He says you're really good at handling cases.

387
00:27:58,880 --> 00:27:59,799
So, you're Shanshan?

388
00:28:00,359 --> 00:28:00,720
Have a seat.

389
00:28:04,319 --> 00:28:05,519
I need to tell you something.

390
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:08,000
Do you know that based on your current actions,

391
00:28:08,319 --> 00:28:09,200
you could be suspected

392
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,720
as a criminal offense?

393
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:15,200
What do you mean?

394
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,640
I don't understand.

395
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,759
Don't be frightened by him.

396
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:20,240
He's kidding.

397
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,839
He likes to make fun.

398
00:28:23,079 --> 00:28:23,839
It's his occupational disease.

399
00:28:23,839 --> 00:28:25,559
He wants to sue anyone he meets.

400
00:28:27,319 --> 00:28:28,160
You drank fake wine,
and you don't even know

401
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:29,759
you were cheated.
What fake wine?

402
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,440
You didn't drink.

403
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,799
Why are you talking nonsense?

404
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:35,039
A bottle of ordinary wine

405
00:28:35,039 --> 00:28:36,519
costing 300 or 500 yuan.

406
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,599
With a label and repackaging,

407
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:40,039
it sells for 26,000 yuan.

408
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:41,279
How much commission?

409
00:28:42,559 --> 00:28:43,119
I'm not asking you.

410
00:28:48,839 --> 00:28:49,640
Lawyer Xu,

411
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:51,920
we've just met today.

412
00:28:52,839 --> 00:28:54,160
I don't understand why

413
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,319
you're so malicious towards me.

414
00:28:55,319 --> 00:28:57,880
But I'm really into Mao.

415
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,720
She's really nice.

416
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:01,279
Really?

417
00:29:02,519 --> 00:29:03,160
For the sake of Liu Mao

418
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:04,480
being really into you,

419
00:29:04,839 --> 00:29:05,640
I'll give you

420
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,240
some free advice as a lawyer.

421
00:29:08,039 --> 00:29:09,039
Intentionally producing

422
00:29:09,039 --> 00:29:10,160
and selling inferior products.

423
00:29:10,559 --> 00:29:11,839
The bill today

424
00:29:12,119 --> 00:29:13,200
is enough to convict you.

425
00:29:16,039 --> 00:29:16,960
What evidence do you have?

426
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,720
The wine is physical evidence.

427
00:29:19,519 --> 00:29:20,680
The transaction records

428
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:21,559
between you and the restaurant manager

429
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:22,559
are documentary evidence.

430
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,640
I don't know what you're talking about.

431
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,319
Lawyer Xu.

432
00:29:31,119 --> 00:29:32,079
I don't know
the manager at all.

433
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:34,839
And if there's a problem with the wine,

434
00:29:34,839 --> 00:29:35,880
it's the restaurant's fault.

435
00:29:37,079 --> 00:29:38,279
I'm also a victim.

436
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:39,480
Yeah.

437
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:40,839
Then I...

438
00:29:41,319 --> 00:29:43,079
We are all victims.

439
00:29:43,079 --> 00:29:44,519
You are a victim, but she's not.

440
00:29:45,079 --> 00:29:46,440
I just checked the wine glass.

441
00:29:47,279 --> 00:29:48,160
If you drank it,
you are a victim.

442
00:29:49,640 --> 00:29:51,119
How can you talk to me

443
00:29:51,119 --> 00:29:51,960
so clearly?

444
00:29:52,759 --> 00:29:53,440
Besides,

445
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:55,680
the water stain below...

446
00:29:58,400 --> 00:29:59,079
Shanshan,

447
00:30:00,359 --> 00:30:02,039
I'm a bit confused now.

448
00:30:02,039 --> 00:30:02,880
I heard

449
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,559
he said about the wine glass

450
00:30:05,559 --> 00:30:06,759
and

451
00:30:06,759 --> 00:30:08,480
the water stain on the ground.

452
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:09,359
What does it mean?

453
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:11,279
Mao, I didn't.

454
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:12,440
I...

455
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,160
Tell me the truth.

456
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,240
Did you lie to me?

457
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:21,640
I'm sorry. I...

458
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:23,759
You are a good person.

459
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:29,359
Shanshan, where are you going?

460
00:30:31,599 --> 00:30:32,039
Go.

461
00:30:32,839 --> 00:30:33,359
Wait.

462
00:30:36,799 --> 00:30:37,200
I've been

463
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:38,480
listening to you for a long time.

464
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:40,119
Don't think you can fool me
by saying that.

465
00:30:41,559 --> 00:30:42,400
I'm telling you,

466
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:43,559
no one can leave

467
00:30:44,119 --> 00:30:44,960
until the bill is settled.

468
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:47,039
Sit for a while.

469
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:51,000
Then don't go.

470
00:30:52,039 --> 00:30:52,720
Passing off fake as real

471
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:53,839
is already a violation of the Criminal Law,

472
00:30:53,839 --> 00:30:54,799
Article 140.

473
00:30:55,359 --> 00:30:56,319
Wine fraud,

474
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,480
intimidating consumers.

475
00:30:58,440 --> 00:30:59,960
Every word you just said

476
00:31:00,559 --> 00:31:01,519
has been recorded.

477
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:03,559
Recording is not allowed in our restaurant.

478
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:04,839
You are infringing on our privacy.

479
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:06,119
You...

480
00:31:06,319 --> 00:31:07,319
If you want it, just take it.

481
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:08,960
All the recordings

482
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,880
have been uploaded to the cloud storage.

483
00:31:11,839 --> 00:31:12,960
And I know better than you

484
00:31:13,319 --> 00:31:14,400
that legal evidence collection

485
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:15,640
is still an infringement of privacy.

486
00:31:15,839 --> 00:31:16,440
One more thing.

487
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,240
I've already called the police.

488
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:19,799
They'll be here
in a few minutes.

489
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:22,240
If you have anything to say,

490
00:31:22,759 --> 00:31:23,920
just tell them.

491
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:24,559
You...

492
00:31:29,599 --> 00:31:30,960
When did you call the police?

493
00:31:33,759 --> 00:31:34,359
Just now,

494
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:36,759
before getting in the car.

495
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:40,680
You are indeed a cunning old fox.

496
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:48,519
Are you okay?

497
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,000
I'm fine.

498
00:31:55,519 --> 00:31:58,400
Since ancient times, heroes have always fallen for beauties.

499
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:02,319
This time, you have definitely

500
00:32:02,319 --> 00:32:03,839
taken a different path

501
00:32:03,839 --> 00:32:05,640
and become a hero.

502
00:32:07,079 --> 00:32:07,880
You can still joke around.

503
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:09,319
It seems that there is no problem.

504
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:10,200
I'm fine.

505
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:12,680
I'm just a little hungry.

506
00:32:13,240 --> 00:32:14,400
The whole meal

507
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:15,599
was eaten by that girl.

508
00:32:18,839 --> 00:32:19,960
Shanshan said she was hungry,

509
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,359
so I gave her all my steak.

510
00:32:21,359 --> 00:32:22,799
I was too busy drinking.

511
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:26,559
Did you eat anything?

512
00:32:26,759 --> 00:32:27,920
You're really not helping.

513
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,319
If you were ten minutes later,

514
00:32:29,319 --> 00:32:30,319
I would have eaten.

515
00:32:32,319 --> 00:32:34,440
Then let me treat you to something.

516
00:32:37,039 --> 00:32:37,640
After the police come
and finish the record,

517
00:32:38,839 --> 00:32:39,559
let's grab a late-night snack.

518
00:32:40,759 --> 00:32:41,240
Sure,

519
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:45,200
but let's find a cheaper place this time.

520
00:33:03,559 --> 00:33:04,519
Song,

521
00:33:07,759 --> 00:33:09,319
I've had enough heartbreak.

522
00:33:11,359 --> 00:33:12,240
Why is dating

523
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,559
so hard?

524
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:20,559
It's not heartbreak

525
00:33:20,559 --> 00:33:21,720
you're dealing with,

526
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,200
it's being conned.

527
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:25,200
As a lawyer,

528
00:33:25,559 --> 00:33:26,960
you got tricked by a bar scammer.

529
00:33:27,279 --> 00:33:28,519
Don't tell people tomorrow

530
00:33:28,519 --> 00:33:29,599
that you are a partner of Zhikun.

531
00:33:32,039 --> 00:33:32,839
What's wrong with a lawyer?

532
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:34,960
Don't lawyers have feelings?

533
00:33:36,799 --> 00:33:37,920
You said she was a scammer.

534
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:39,599
To trick me,

535
00:33:40,279 --> 00:33:41,960
she made up such a story.

536
00:33:42,759 --> 00:33:43,599
From

537
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:45,960
another perspective,

538
00:33:47,119 --> 00:33:47,920
doesn't that mean

539
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:49,000
she likes me a bit?

540
00:33:49,559 --> 00:33:50,680
She put a lot of effort into it.

541
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:53,240
You're still not getting the message.

542
00:34:01,279 --> 00:34:02,480
So, I'm just

543
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:05,240
a cog in the wheel?

544
00:34:06,839 --> 00:34:07,920
At this point,

545
00:34:08,159 --> 00:34:08,880
just let it go.

546
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:22,199
If she doesn't like me,

547
00:34:23,079 --> 00:34:24,239
why would she chat with me

548
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:25,239
when I'm feeling down?

549
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,440
Wasn't that you

550
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:27,480
texting her first?

551
00:34:27,719 --> 00:34:28,760
And when I said I wanted something sweet,

552
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:30,440
she made it for me herself!

553
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:31,199
But you were the one

554
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:32,280
who said you wanted it.

555
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:38,559
So all this sweetness

556
00:34:38,559 --> 00:34:39,679
was just me asking for it?

557
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:41,239
It's all just one-sided?

558
00:34:41,599 --> 00:34:42,760
What's wrong with asking?

559
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:44,960
Just because you asked for candy

560
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,039
doesn't mean it's not candy.

561
00:34:47,079 --> 00:34:47,880
Just because you asked for candy
doesn't mean it's not sweet.

562
00:34:50,079 --> 00:34:50,880
It's candy.

563
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:52,719
Just eat it.

564
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:57,639
Since you enjoyed the process,

565
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,679
don't care about the result.

566
00:35:00,039 --> 00:35:00,960
I worked so hard
to maintain the process.

567
00:35:01,960 --> 00:35:03,119
Isn't it because I want a

568
00:35:03,119 --> 00:35:04,159
good result?

569
00:35:06,519 --> 00:35:07,199
When they were talking about me,

570
00:35:07,199 --> 00:35:08,400
you were pretty cool.

571
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:10,719
When you heard that

572
00:35:10,719 --> 00:35:11,639
the novel ended,
didn't you

573
00:35:12,039 --> 00:35:12,960
feel bad for two days?

574
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,159
[Next week is New Year's Eve.]

575
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,280
[Students who want to exchange gifts,]

576
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:45,559
[please hand them over to the Culture and Entertainment Department.]

577
00:35:46,039 --> 00:35:47,199
[The department will organize a drawing of lots]

578
00:35:47,199 --> 00:35:48,679
[the day before New Year's Eve.]

579
00:36:24,679 --> 00:36:25,719
Don't even think about it.

580
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:27,559
The kids are still so young.

581
00:36:27,559 --> 00:36:28,800
How can they go to America with you?

582
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:31,480
I'm discussing this with you, aren't I?

583
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:33,679
You should at least ask

584
00:36:33,679 --> 00:36:34,599
the kids' opinion.

585
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:35,840
No need to ask.

586
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,679
Huai Shi won't go with you.

587
00:38:37,079 --> 00:38:37,920
Brother.

588
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:43,960
Brother.

589
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:49,480
Mom and Dad are going to...

590
00:38:50,199 --> 00:38:51,840
Going to divorce.

591
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:54,440
I know.

592
00:38:55,239 --> 00:38:56,519
Don't cry. Don't cry.

593
00:38:58,480 --> 00:38:59,760
Let's go back to our room, okay?

594
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:21,920
Brother.

595
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:24,480
From now on,

596
00:39:25,239 --> 00:39:26,519
can we only

597
00:39:26,519 --> 00:39:28,519
have one of them?

598
00:39:30,519 --> 00:39:34,239
Mom said Dad was going to America.

599
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:37,320
She asked me if I wanted to go.

600
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:45,400
I don't want to go that far away.

601
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:49,400
I don't know anyone there.

602
00:39:50,559 --> 00:39:54,800
I don't want to go with Dad.

603
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:21,320
I won't let you go to America.

604
00:40:23,079 --> 00:40:24,239
Really?

605
00:40:33,119 --> 00:40:33,760
Really.

606
00:40:35,079 --> 00:40:35,599
Don't cry.

607
00:40:56,599 --> 00:40:57,280
Brother.

608
00:40:58,039 --> 00:40:59,239
What's that?

609
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:19,360
It's a gift.

610
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:45,360
for you.

611
00:41:57,480 --> 00:41:58,960
[If I hadn't backed down,]

612
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,480
[would the outcome have been different?]

613
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:31,199
Brother, will Sister Ruan Yu's case

614
00:42:31,199 --> 00:42:32,800
go to court tomorrow?

615
00:42:35,079 --> 00:42:36,239
I'll go and cheer her up,

616
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:36,960
and give her some support.

617
00:42:37,679 --> 00:42:38,960
The trial is about to start.

618
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:40,880
How are things going with Ruan Yu?

619
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:42,519
It's going well.

620
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:43,440
Don't worry about it.

621
00:42:46,239 --> 00:42:47,320
When I asked you yesterday,

622
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:48,239
you were still upset.

623
00:42:48,719 --> 00:42:50,039
You've figured it out today?

624
00:42:50,599 --> 00:42:52,280
The novel's ending was her idea before.

625
00:42:52,599 --> 00:42:53,400
It doesn't mean the present,

626
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:54,760
let alone the future.

627
00:42:58,039 --> 00:42:59,880
One night's reflection, and you're a different person.

628
00:43:00,519 --> 00:43:01,280
Impressive.

629
00:43:01,719 --> 00:43:03,039
The sky's cleared, the rain's stopped,

630
00:43:03,400 --> 00:43:04,280
and my brother's back on track.

631
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:06,360
What about you?

632
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:07,519
Your homeroom teacher

633
00:43:07,519 --> 00:43:08,760
sent me your last month's

634
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:09,400
your monthly exam results.

635
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:11,320
They don't look good.

636
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:14,679
I'm busy. Bye.

637
00:43:30,039 --> 00:43:30,960
Another post

638
00:43:31,519 --> 00:43:33,039
from Sister Ruan Yu.

639
00:43:38,639 --> 00:43:39,639
Giving it my all

640
00:43:39,639 --> 00:43:40,880
and trying without regrets

641
00:43:41,280 --> 00:43:43,079
is a kind of fulfillment.

642
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:45,239
You've got

643
00:43:45,239 --> 00:43:47,079
a point, Song.

644
00:43:48,920 --> 00:43:51,719
Backing down means regrets.

645
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:55,320
But if we fight for it,

646
00:43:57,159 --> 00:43:58,360
we'll be able to

647
00:43:58,360 --> 00:44:00,000
justify our feelings.

648
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:03,320
It's like a lawsuit.

649
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:05,599
No matter the outcome,

650
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:08,760
just do it.

651
00:44:28,440 --> 00:44:30,280
Xu Huaisong actually likes posts?

652
00:44:31,159 --> 00:44:32,800
Never seen him like Liu Mao's.

653
00:44:33,719 --> 00:44:34,320
So

654
00:44:34,519 --> 00:44:35,760
he does browse WeChat Moments?

655
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:55,880
[I'll pick you up at 7 a.m. tomorrow.]

656
00:45:00,199 --> 00:45:01,199
This must be

657
00:45:02,079 --> 00:45:03,519
the last time we meet, right?

658
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:10,639
Since the defendant

659
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:11,719
didn't show up,

660
00:45:12,639 --> 00:45:14,760
and the plaintiff

661
00:45:15,360 --> 00:45:16,719
refused mediation,

662
00:45:17,679 --> 00:45:19,440
we'll postpone the ruling.

663
00:45:20,199 --> 00:45:22,400
The decision will be mailed

664
00:45:22,400 --> 00:45:23,119
to both parties.

665
00:45:23,679 --> 00:45:24,519
Court adjourned.

666
00:45:27,960 --> 00:45:28,480
Ms. Cen,

667
00:45:29,079 --> 00:45:30,199
I did my best.

668
00:45:30,800 --> 00:45:32,280
The plaintiff insisted on not mediating.

669
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,159
Based on today's hearing,

670
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:35,599
the court is likely to
support her claim.

671
00:45:38,199 --> 00:45:38,800
Okay.

672
00:45:41,159 --> 00:45:41,760
I see.

673
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:12,800
It should be fine, right, Lawyer Xu?

674
00:46:13,400 --> 00:46:14,039
Don't worry.

675
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:15,440
If all goes well, you'll receive

676
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:16,320
the judgment within a month.

677
00:46:16,880 --> 00:46:18,000
Once it's published online,

678
00:46:18,239 --> 00:46:18,960
this matter

679
00:46:19,079 --> 00:46:20,159
will be completely resolved.

680
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:22,000
That's good.

681
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:23,480
Sorry
to keep you waiting.

682
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:25,239
My old problem.

683
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:26,440
I always have diarrhea

684
00:46:26,679 --> 00:46:27,519
after court.

685
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:30,599
I need to practice my mentality.

686
00:46:31,519 --> 00:46:32,360
All right, let's go.

687
00:46:32,679 --> 00:46:33,719
The enemy has been defeated.

688
00:46:33,719 --> 00:46:35,239
We can go back

689
00:46:35,480 --> 00:46:36,320
and rest.

690
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:37,119
Let's go.
Go.

691
00:46:44,039 --> 00:46:44,760
Hello, Mingying.
Check Weibo.

692
00:46:46,559 --> 00:46:47,599
Cen Sisi committed suicide.

693
00:46:47,599 --> 00:46:48,519
Many netizens are guessing

694
00:46:48,519 --> 00:46:49,599
that you forced her to do it.

695
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:54,480
What's wrong?

696
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:00,719
Cen Sisi

697
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:02,519
committed suicide.

698
00:47:25,679 --> 00:47:27,119
One fried dough stick, two eggs,

699
00:47:27,719 --> 00:47:28,320
and a cup of soy milk.

700
00:47:30,400 --> 00:47:31,639
The fried dough stick should be soft.

701
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:33,119
Fried dough stick and eggs are the best.

702
00:47:33,320 --> 00:47:34,679
Lawyer Xu, you also believe in this?

703
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:37,039
Boss,

704
00:47:37,159 --> 00:47:38,440
I want a dough stick and two eggs.

705
00:47:40,559 --> 00:47:41,559
In junior high,
a dough stick and two eggs

706
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:43,559
can get 100 points.

707
00:47:43,559 --> 00:47:44,480
Now in senior high,

708
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:45,599
Chinese, math, and English are all 150 points.

709
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:47,440
Aren't politics, history, and geography still 100 points?

710
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:48,559
Besides,

711
00:47:48,800 --> 00:47:49,639
my 100

712
00:47:49,639 --> 00:47:51,079
also means 100 percent.

713
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:52,719
I'm sending a signal

714
00:47:52,719 --> 00:47:53,480
to my brain

715
00:47:53,800 --> 00:47:54,880
to give it more energy

716
00:47:54,880 --> 00:47:56,320
and intelligence to face the exam.

717
00:47:57,320 --> 00:47:57,800
Do you understand?

718
00:47:58,639 --> 00:47:59,119
Give me money.

719
00:47:59,119 --> 00:48:00,199
More intelligence.

720
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:03,719
I used to believe this,
and I was even laughed at.

721
00:48:05,280 --> 00:48:06,840
Boss, I want one too.

722
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:08,280
This one is for you.

723
00:48:10,039 --> 00:48:11,599
Lawyer Xu, don't you eat it yourself?

724
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:13,719
My breakfast hasn't arrived yet.

725
00:48:14,840 --> 00:48:15,920
Thank you. One more douhua,

726
00:48:15,960 --> 00:48:16,559
and an egg.
How much?

727
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:19,320
25 yuan.
Okay, thank you.

728
00:48:23,880 --> 00:48:24,719
Morning, Ruan Yu, Lawyer Liu.

729
00:48:25,880 --> 00:48:26,239
Okay.
I've paid for the breakfast.

730
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:28,280
Have a seat.

731
00:48:29,320 --> 00:48:30,119
Come on.

732
00:48:31,960 --> 00:48:33,119
This is for you. It's good for your brain.

733
00:48:37,639 --> 00:48:38,599
And yours.

734
00:48:46,199 --> 00:48:46,840
By the way,

735
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:48,719
can you show me

736
00:48:48,880 --> 00:48:49,719
the trial materials again?

737
00:48:50,159 --> 00:48:51,519
I want to review them

738
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:52,679
to feel more prepared.

739
00:48:53,039 --> 00:48:53,960
Sure.

740
00:48:54,880 --> 00:48:55,679
It's in my bag.

741
00:48:56,079 --> 00:48:56,400
Okay.

742
00:49:02,400 --> 00:49:03,159
Not that one.

743
00:49:03,719 --> 00:49:04,400
That's the other side's.

744
00:49:06,119 --> 00:49:07,199
It's just the tip of the iceberg.

745
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:08,559
can you tell the difference?

746
00:49:09,199 --> 00:49:09,679
Is it because they

747
00:49:09,679 --> 00:49:10,719
have different thickness?

748
00:49:11,320 --> 00:49:12,199
Because that clip

749
00:49:13,880 --> 00:49:14,519
is yellow.

750
00:49:18,880 --> 00:49:20,880
So, this green clip

751
00:49:20,880 --> 00:49:22,159
is for our own file,

752
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:24,039
which means green light all the way.

753
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:25,280
Smart.

754
00:49:27,239 --> 00:49:28,760
Do lawyers believe in these things?

755
00:49:30,239 --> 00:49:31,559
Or is it because my case

756
00:49:31,559 --> 00:49:32,280
is rather complicated,

757
00:49:32,280 --> 00:49:33,320
So it needs

758
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:33,960
more luck.

759
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:35,480
This case

760
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:37,239
is indeed a small one.

761
00:49:37,639 --> 00:49:38,400
But

762
00:49:39,559 --> 00:49:41,000
we have a lawyer

763
00:49:41,000 --> 00:49:42,639
who always fulfills the wishes

764
00:49:42,639 --> 00:49:43,519
of her clients.

765
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:45,320
I saw your post on WeChat yesterday.

766
00:49:46,000 --> 00:49:47,880
You wanted a lucky charm.

767
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:49,639
So here you are.

768
00:49:52,320 --> 00:49:53,599
Did you sleep well last night?

769
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:56,880
It's your first lawsuit,

770
00:49:57,400 --> 00:49:58,639
so you must be a little nervous, right?

771
00:50:01,119 --> 00:50:01,840
But

772
00:50:02,039 --> 00:50:03,480
I have two great lawyers backing me up.

773
00:50:03,840 --> 00:50:04,599
Even the file holders

774
00:50:04,599 --> 00:50:05,840
are taken care of.

775
00:50:07,039 --> 00:50:07,880
I feel very reassured.

776
00:50:08,320 --> 00:50:09,159
I slept very well last night.

777
00:50:10,760 --> 00:50:11,519
With this mindset,
our case

778
00:50:13,079 --> 00:50:13,559
is bound to win.
